Update collection relation fields using Fibery collection commands.
This tool supports adding relation items via `fibery.entity/add-collection-items`.

Use this tool for add operations when updating collection relation fields (for example, assignees) instead of `update_entity`.

Example: Add assignee to a card
{
    "database": "Kanban/Card",
    "entity_id": "ea5a9b77-d16b-4bdc-b4f2-5dad6764ad0f",
    "field": "assignments/assignees",
    "operation": "add",
    "item_ids": [
        "f2a89e59-6a5a-439c-ab10-5e376548e8c9"
    ]
}

To remove/unlink items from a collection field, use `unlink_collection`.
